Sad,

I've done some work in this direction, although with an object-relational d=
atabase, not an OODB.  I'm convinced that the OODB concept is fatally flawe=
d.

There is no show stopper in the language as far as database implementation =
goes.  Well, there are some issues but nothing that can't be cured by addin=
g a method or two to the file classes.

